<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" box="[151,392,336,360]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">DISTRIBUTION (Fig. 7)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
All studies reporting 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[455,677,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis box="[455,677,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Tibicina haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Valais are considered to be incorrect (
<bibRefCitation author="FUESSLIN, J. C." box="[264,428,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" refId="ref16256" refString="FUESSLIN, J. C. 1775. Verzeichnis der ihm bekannten Schweitzerischen Inseckten. Bey dem Verfasser und in Commission bey Heinrich Steiner und Compagnie, Zurich und Winterthur, XII + 62 pp." type="book" year="1775">Fuesslin, 1775</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="STOLL, O." box="[443,567,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="145 - 208" refId="ref19299" refString="STOLL, O. 1901. Uber xerotherme Relikte in der Schweizer Fauna der Wirbellosen. Jahresberichte der Geographisch-Ethnographischen Gesellschaft in Zurich 2: 145 - 208." type="journal article" year="1901">Stoll, 1901</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="KUNTZE, R." box="[583,733,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="629 - 690" refId="ref17545" refString="KUNTZE, R. 1931. Vergleichende Beobachtungen und Betrachtungen uber die xerotherme Fauna in Podolien, Brandenburg, Osterreich und der Schweiz. Zeitschrift fur Morphologie und Okologie der Tiere 21: 629 - 690." type="journal article" year="1931">Kuntze, 1931</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="SCHEDL, W." box="[748,893,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="257 - 271" refId="ref18896" refString="SCHEDL, W. 2000. Taxonomie, Biologie und Verbreitung der Singzikaden Mitteleuropas (Insecta: Homoptera: Cicadidae et Tibicinidae). Berichte des naturwissenschaftlichmedizinischen Vereins Innsbruck 87: 257 - 271." type="journal article" year="2000">Schedl, 2000</bibRefCitation>
) as well as two voucher specimens labelled with “ 
<collectingCountry box="[542,614,430,454]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Wallis</collectingCountry>
” (NMT) and “Martigny” (VS, MNHN). Nevertheless, it is possible that the species could have reached 
<collectingCountry box="[827,954,462,486]" name="Switzerland" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
from three different directions historically,from the north, the south or the west, since it has been published for all neighbouring countries except 
<collectingCountry box="[698,846,525,549]" name="Liechtenstein" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Liechtenstein</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[862,911,525,549]" name="Italy" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Italy</collectingCountry>
[up to Bozen (
<bibRefCitation author="SCHEDL, W." box="[159,310,556,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref18931" refString="SCHEDL, W. 2002. Die Verbreitung der funf Singzikaden-Arten in Osterreich (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea). Denisia 04: 231 - 239." type="book chapter" year="2002">Schedl, 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and around Torino (
<bibRefCitation author="GRIFFINI, A." box="[571,733,556,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="143 - 144" refId="ref16566" refString="GRIFFINI, A. 1896. Notes sur la faune entomologique piemontaise. X. Cicadidae, Membracidae et Scaridae. Miscellanea Entomologica. Revue Entomologique Internationale 4 (11 - 12): 143 - 144." type="journal article" year="1896">Griffini, 1896</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DELLA BEFFA, G." box="[752,965,556,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="141 - 147" refId="ref15885" refString="DELLA BEFFA, G. 1925. Contributo alla conoscenza della fauna entomologica del Piemonte: Omotteri (Emitteri). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana 57: 141 - 147." type="journal article" year="1925">Della Beffa, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)], 
<collectingCountry box="[1001,1074,557,580]" name="France" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">France</collectingCountry>
[including central parts (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="HAGEN, H." box="[473,615,588,613]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref16703" refString="HAGEN, H. 1855. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 16: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="1855">Hagen, 1855</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="PUISSANT, S." box="[630,795,588,612]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" refId="ref18488" refString="PUISSANT, S. 2006. Contribution ala connaissance des cigales de France: Geonemie et ecologie des populations (Hemiptera, Cicadidae). Association pour la Caracterisation et l'Etude des Entomocenoses, Bedeilhac et Aynat, 193 pp." type="book" year="2006">Puissant, 2006</bibRefCitation>
)], 
<collectingCountry box="[822,901,588,612]" name="Austria" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Austria</collectingCountry>
[
<collectingRegion box="[917,1073,588,612]" country="Austria" name="Wien" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Vienna region</collectingRegion>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="HAGEN, H." box="[206,346,619,644]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref16703" refString="HAGEN, H. 1855. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 16: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="1855">Hagen, 1855</bibRefCitation>
; Wagner &amp;Franz, 1961; 
<bibRefCitation author="SCHEDL, W." box="[611,755,619,643]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref18931" refString="SCHEDL, W. 2002. Die Verbreitung der funf Singzikaden-Arten in Osterreich (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea). Denisia 04: 231 - 239." type="book chapter" year="2002">Schedl, 2002</bibRefCitation>
)] and 
<collectingCountry box="[822,921,619,643]" name="Germany" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Germany</collectingCountry>
[Rhine-Main region (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="HAGEN, H." box="[281,421,651,676]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref16703" refString="HAGEN, H. 1855. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 16: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="1855">Hagen, 1855</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="VOGEL, R." box="[433,564,651,675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="146 - 154" refId="ref19812" refString="VOGEL, R. 1935. Die blutrote Singzikade (Tibicen haematodes Scop.) in Wurttemberg und Deutschland. Jahreshefte des Vereins fur vaterlandische Naturkunde in Wurttemberg 91: 146 - 154." type="journal article" year="1935">Vogel, 1935</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="VOGEL, R." box="[576,632,651,675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="116 - 123" refId="ref19846" refString="VOGEL, R. 1937. Weiteres uber Verbreitung und Lebensweise der Blutroten Singzikade (Tibicen haematodes Scop.). Jahreshefte des Vereins fur vaterlandische Naturkunde in Wurttemberg 93: 116 - 123." type="journal article" year="1937">1937</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="SCHWOERBEL, W." box="[644,843,651,675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="462 - 560" refId="ref19056" refString="SCHWOERBEL, W. 1957. Die Wanzen und Zikaden des Spitzberges bei Tubingen, eine faunistisch-okologische Untersuchung (Hemipteroidea: Heteroptera und Cicadina = Homoptera Auchenorrhyncha). Zeitschrift fur Morphologie und Okologie der Tiere, Berlin 45: 462 - 560." type="journal article" year="1957">Schwoerbel, 1957</bibRefCitation>
)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
With respect to the north, Labram &amp;Imhoff(1845) mentioned 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[918,1066,682,706]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis box="[918,1066,682,706]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as avery rare species in the Basel region. One historic population is mentioned from the vineyards in Rouffach (
<collectingRegion box="[470,547,745,769]" country="France" name="Alsace" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Alsace</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[565,639,745,769]" name="France" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">France</collectingCountry>
) situated only 
<quantity box="[819,894,745,769]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" unit="km" value="50.0">50 km</quantity>
north of Basel (
<bibRefCitation author="DODERLEIN, L." box="[158,336,777,801]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="163 - 174" refId="ref15944" refString="DODERLEIN, L. 1913. Beobachtungen uber elsassische Tiere. Mitteilungen der Philomathischen Gesellschaft in Elsass-Lothringen, Strassbourg 5 (1): 163 - 174." type="journal article" year="1913">Döderlein, 1913</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="HUBER, A." box="[348,479,777,801]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref17373" refString="HUBER, A. 1916. Die warmeliebende Tierwelt der weitern Umgebung Basels. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Berlin, Abteilung A 82 (7): 1 - 120." type="journal article" year="1916">Huber,1916</bibRefCitation>
). 
<specimenCount box="[497,641,777,801]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="generic">16 specimens</specimenCount>
of this time are deposited in the collection of the Zoological Museum of Strasbourg labelled with the nearby village of Westhalten (
<bibRefCitation author="HUGEL, S. &amp; ATT, F. &amp; ALLOT, H. &amp; ELDTRAUER, J. &amp; RUA, C." box="[286,484,840,864]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="5 - 10" refId="ref17430" refString="HUGEL, S., M ATT, F., C ALLOT, H., F ELDTRAUER, J. &amp; B RUA, C. 2008. Presence de Cicadetta brevipennis Fieber, 1876 en Alsace (Hemiptera, Cicadidae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de Mulhouse, 64 (1): 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hugel 
<emphasis box="[362,418,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">et al.</emphasis>
,2008
</bibRefCitation>
). The German population nearest to 
<collectingCountry box="[889,1016,840,864]" name="Switzerland" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
was described from Tübingen (Baden-Württemberg) with apopulation of 80 to 
<specimenCount pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="generic">100 specimens</specimenCount>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SCHWOERBEL, W." box="[243,444,902,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="462 - 560" refId="ref19056" refString="SCHWOERBEL, W. 1957. Die Wanzen und Zikaden des Spitzberges bei Tubingen, eine faunistisch-okologische Untersuchung (Hemipteroidea: Heteroptera und Cicadina = Homoptera Auchenorrhyncha). Zeitschrift fur Morphologie und Okologie der Tiere, Berlin 45: 462 - 560." type="journal article" year="1957">Schwoerbel, 1957</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="FISCHER, L. H." box="[465,624,902,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="237 - 243" refId="ref16236" refString="FISCHER, L. H. 1847. Ueber Sing-Cicaden. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 8: 237 - 243." type="journal article" year="1847">Fischer (1847)</bibRefCitation>
cited an occurrence from Tuttlingen and Immendingen (Baden-Württemberg) that is only situated 
<quantity box="[787,858,934,958]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" unit="km" value="15.0">15 km</quantity>
north of the Swiss border, but had doubts about the identification. To summarize, it is possible that Labram &amp;Imhoff(1845) are correct and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[602,751,997,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis box="[602,751,997,1021]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had sporadically occurred in the Basel region, but nevertheless it is more likely that the authors confused it with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1772" box="[151,281,1061,1084]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[151,281,1061,1084]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">C. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[294,337,1060,1084]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A specimen labelled “Winterthur” (ZH) (1900-1910, leg. Huber, NMWI) is considered as doubtful, since it was near ahandwritten label with “cicada from the Mediterranean for comparison”. The location probably refers to the domicile of the collector.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
With respect to the south, no reliable historic references could be found that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[151,298,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis box="[151,298,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
once occurred in 
<collectingRegion box="[495,567,1218,1242]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ticino</collectingRegion>
. Two unlabelled specimens are deposited in the MCSN collected by Scherrer and Maestri who were active mainly in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[1005,1074,1250,1274]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ticino</collectingRegion>
and especially in the surroundings of Morcote and Melide at the beginning of the 20 
<superScript attach="right" box="[1057,1074,1279,1298]" fontSize="8" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">th</superScript>
century (Pollini Paltrinieri, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<materialsCitation collectorName="They &amp; Ville &amp; Bernex &amp; Simonet &amp; Schauenberg &amp; Maerky &amp; Wetherefore" country="Switzerland" location="Rhone River" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" specimenCount="2" specimenCount-adult="1" specimenCount-female="1" stateProvince="Geneve">
<bibRefCitation author="VERNIER, R." box="[227,384,1346,1370]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="147 - 152" refId="ref19779" refString="VERNIER, R. 1996. Un chanteur isole de Lyristes plebejus (Scop.) (Hemiptera, Cicadidae) a l'Allondon. Bulletin romand d'entomologie 14: 147 - 152." type="journal article" year="1996">Vernier (1996)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned ahistorical occurrence of the species for the 
<collectingRegion country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Geneva region</collectingRegion>
, the most western part of 
<collectingCountry box="[506,637,1378,1402]" name="Switzerland" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
. In fact, 
<specimenCount box="[733,826,1378,1402]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="adult">six adult</specimenCount>
specimens (
<specimenCount box="[964,1006,1378,1402]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
,5 ♁) and four nymphal skins of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[440,587,1410,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis box="[440,587,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion box="[700,895,1410,1434]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Canton of Geneva</collectingRegion>
are preserved in the collection of the MHNG. 
<collectorName box="[510,565,1442,1466]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">They</collectorName>
are labelled from the two localities “Pont Butin/Aïre” (western city limit of 
<collectingRegion box="[534,617,1474,1498]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Geneva</collectingRegion>
) and “Nant de Lagnon” (east of Aire-la- 
<collectorName box="[151,205,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ville</collectorName>
, municipality of 
<collectorName box="[397,476,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Bernex</collectorName>
) (leg. 
<collectorName box="[551,643,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Simonet</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName box="[656,796,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Schauenberg</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName box="[810,893,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Maerky</collectorName>
or anonymous). 
<collectorName box="[151,284,1538,1562]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Wetherefore</collectorName>
conclude that areproductive population must have existed along afour kilometre length of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F087DBFFC1FFAA23FA88E5FC02C189:8E866016FFC1FFAC22F98E24FDBCC500" box="[404,540,1570,1594]" country="Switzerland" name="Rhone River" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" stateProvince="Geneve">Rhone River</location>
from 1914 to 1947
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<materialsCitation location="Rhone River" municipality="Basel region" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Ticino">
Despite recent intense field work, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[594,741,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis box="[594,741,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found neither in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[151,220,1634,1658]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ticino</collectingRegion>
nor in the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[354,496,1634,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Basel region</collectingMunicipality>
. When investigating the slopes of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F087DBFFC1FFAA23FA88E5FC02C189:8E866016FFC1FFAC20C88E64FB91C540" box="[933,1073,1634,1658]" municipality="Basel region" name="Rhone River" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" stateProvince="Ticino">Rhone River</location>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
